  <refnamediv>
    <refname>immatch_Flann</refname>
    <refpurpose>FLANN-based matcher for feature descriptors.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   m = immatch_Flann(des1, des2);
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>des1 :</term>
            <listitem><para>First descriptor matrix.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>des2 :</term>
            <listitem><para>Second descriptor matrix.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>m :</term>
            <listitem><para>Matching matrix. Rows contain query index, train index, image index, and distance.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function matches two descriptor matrices using OpenCV FLANN-based matching. The returned matrix uses Scilab one-based feature indices.
   </para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// Read the image and rotate it by 45 degrees
S = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/balloons_gray.png"));
S2 = imrotate(S, 45);

// Detect ORB features
f1 = imdetect_ORB(S);
f2 = imdetect_ORB(S2);

// Extract descriptors
d1 = imextract_DescriptorORB(S, f1);
d2 = imextract_DescriptorORB(S2, f2);

// Match descriptors with FLANN
m = immatch_Flann(d1, d2);

// Keep the 10 best matches and draw them
[fout1, fout2, mout] = imbestmatches(f1, f2, m, 10);
SS = imdrawmatches(S, S2, fout1, fout2, mout);
imshow(SS);
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

